com.google.flightmap.parsing.faa.amr
Class AviationMasterRecordParser

java.lang.Object
  com.google.flightmap.parsing.faa.amr.AviationMasterRecordParser

public class AviationMasterRecordParser
extends Object

Parses airports from FAA Airport Master Record file and adds them to a SQLite database http://www.faa.gov/airports/airport_safety/airportdata_5010/

rankAirportsInDb

private void rankAirportsInDb()
                       throws SQLException
Iterates over all airports and updates their rank according to their properties. Typically, this should be done after the initial addition of airports with bogus rank (e.g. -1).

Throws:
SQLException
See Also:
computeAirportRank(com.google.flightmap.common.data.Airport)

computeAirportRank

private static int computeAirportRank(Airport airport)
Returns the rank of an airport on a 0 (minor airport) - 5 (major airport) scale. Major factors affecting rank include type, runway length, and surface.

Returns:
Airport rank, 0 (minor airport) - 5 (major airport)

addAirportProperty

private void addAirportProperty(int id,
                                String key,
                                String value)
                         throws SQLException
Adds a property to an airport.

Key is an airport property header, and is mapped to a user friendly label. Both key label and value strings are converted to constants. If the value string can be parsed as an integer, it is not converted.

Parameters:
id - Airport id
key - Property header
value - Property value.
Throws:
SQLException

removeEnclosingQuotes

private static void removeEnclosingQuotes(String[] headers)

[ "\"foo\"", "\"bar\"" ] -> [ "foo", "bar" ]
